docs/operations/MICRO_CHUNK_RISK_BACKLOG.md:390:- F7-4 [low] Confirmation message type decode uses raw assembly without length guard. _decodeMessageType (line 767) uses assembly calldataload on payload.offset without checking payload.length >= 2. A zero-length or 1-byte payload would be accepted without revert, returning messageType = 0 (which hits the `messageType != MSG_TYPE_BRIDGE_TRANSFER` revert path). In the current call path _lzReceive validates payload enough before calling this, but if the decoding logic is reused the missing guard could mask malformed messages.
